data.title: Trevor Thompson Cut After Agreeing to Warriors Contract on Friday

data.text:
Melissa Majchrzak/Getty Images

The Golden State Warriors announced Friday that they have cut center Trevor Thompson just hours after signing the big man to a contract.

Thompson was not selected in the 2017 NBA draft after averaging 10.6 points, 9.2 rebounds and 1.5 blocks per game at Ohio State last season.

The 23-year-old played for the Boston Celtics in Las Vegas Summer League, averaging 2.3 points and 1.5 rebounds per contest.
